& [SLMProviderDisagreementPayloadContract] is the contract for typed provider objections and answers
  + [contract_uuid] is 6b64fb05-9b1f-43c6-82d1-9b4d17294a41
  + [slice_id] is SLM-26
  + [status] is source_implemented_policy_gated

  & [Purpose] is to keep lower-LLM disagreement articulated instead of flattened
    = must: allow objecting providers to name the disagreement class
    = must: allow supporting providers to name the answer kind
    = must: preserve rationale and provider provenance separately
    = must: let deliberation consume typed payloads without assuming all objections are role conflicts
    - never: turn disagreement into a vague score bump without objection and answer lineage

  & [ProviderObjectionPayload] is the objection evidence payload
    + [disagreement_class] is same_meaning_different_words, role_conflict, relation_conflict, scope_conflict, unsupported_claim, contradiction, insufficient_context, invalid_consequence, or lineage_gap
    + [rationale] is required
    + [target_ref] is required
    + [provider_provenance] is required

  & [ProviderAnswerPayload] is the answer evidence payload
    + [answer_kind] is resolves, narrows, reframes, concedes, rejects, or defers
    + [rationale] is required
    + [target_ref] is required
    + [provider_provenance] is required

  & [RuntimeProjection] is provider suggestion fields consumed by deliberation
    + [provider_source] is slm_rust/src/providers.rs
    + [deliberation_consumer] is slm_rust/src/deliberation.rs
    + [status] is source_complete_policy_gated
